The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 May is 42,152 (4,878.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 May, there were 110 new confirmed cases (12.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 May, there were 105 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (5 extra cases).
